values:
We used to see things from a similar perspective...


We used to be a Team...



We used to have the best times together...



Will it ever be the same?

I fucking hate Facebook....

WHY can't i just use the computer without checking it?

Fuck you Facebook.

People can be really fucking nasty to each other. I don't know why i feel the need to say this like i've never known it before but somehow, i feel like people are getting nastier with each other. My friends are bitching about each other, cheating on each other and lying to each other. I know too much! I don't want to know anymore shit about other people... My life is going along just fine and i'd like to keep it that way. I feel like the more i know about my friends and the secrets they're failing to keep, the more i become involved by default.
Ignorance just might be bliss this time i think.

So i'm spending a lot of time at home and in places where i don't have to be around a lot of people. Ever since i got back from the coast, i've felt the need to be away from chit-chat and gossip. I've managed to be sick 2 weekends in a row so i've had no choice but to stay home in my pj's... Which i'm actually really enjoying.

I hate the facebook.... i love the facebook. I'm trying to stay away from it but i've just uploaded my first photo album so i feel really stupid AND clever at the same time. Well... it's passing the time, at least. It's giving me an opportunity to re-connect with people i've lost touch with. Then again, i'm really shit at keeping in touch with people. I haven't even updated my own journal for three weeks... There were 33 unread emails in my inbox today! THIRTY THREE!!! -(mostly msgs from fucking facebook)- Ahh well, again, it pases the time...

I wonder what life would be like if we never felt the need to pass the time? Maybe one day we can all have the opportunity to do what we love in life instead of trying to find ways to pass the time while we're stuck doing things we don't really enjoy. Seriously... time is precious. The more i keep reminding myself that, the more i might just realise it. I gotta go get some sleep so i can get up tomorrow and do something that makes me happy instead of sitting here typing to no one...

Went to the Bower at Broulee on a much needed quiet getaway...


Ate breakfast surrounded by trees, birds and a rare species of Pat...


Tried to climb some trees... but they were too tall....


Went rock surfing...


And did a lot of holiday smiling...
(We were also lucky enough to encounter an endangered sugar glider that jumped out of a tree next to our bungalow and glided over us while we watched in awe... Awesome.)

Have you ever had an itch so strong that the satisfaction of scratching the absolute shit out of it was almost orgasmic?
If not then it sucks to be you.
If so, then you can probably guess how well the next few days are going to flow for me.

I've had this itch for too long. I want to see the sunrise from the top of a mountain and have no one else there (except maybe that one special person should he desire to join me)! I want to walk along a beach and get sand in my shoes. I want to feel the crisp air that only breezes in on a coastal frequency. I need to get away for a little while.... But i'll be back... and happier.

I'm off to a coastal tree house with a spa and a fireplace. I'm only  taking things that make me happy. 
I'm ready. I'm set... and in 12 hours i'll be GONE!

Looking very forward to it.

Im at Ashleys house... YAY!!!
But now i have to go because i took too long to get online and everyone's ready to leave.
YAY!!!
You can do something in an instant that will change your life forever...

I don't know how i feel about this....

If a stupid little girl sits alone at her computer for too long and slowly turns in to a house plant.... Does she make a sound?

I'm sick of being sick... My body refuses to cooperate with me. Everything that goes in must come out i guess... but does it have to come out the same way it went in?

I'm also sick of being so unproductive. I'm sick of having such a high standard of productivity. I'm too hard on myself and i'm sick of that most of all. It's not enough for me to start and finish 4 new songs in 6 weeks... What's the point if no one ever hears them? What's that point of playing in my room to imaginary audiences anyway? What's the point of doing what i'm doing? Do i even like my own voice anymore? Argh.... I think i'm just sick and run-down so i'm using up the last of my energy to be upset about my situation instead of trying to make it better.

It's alright. I'll figure something out... I usually do.

Remember this dickhead?




From the Lions Riot
(artwork courtesy of Mikey)

This is Mad.



She's coming back in 2 days.
Hurry up already...
I can't decide whether or not i want to look like that when i'm eating bickies...

The night before
my trashy, broken Sunday
keeps me coming back...

After midnight, the transformation begins....



Yep... I'm still bored...

I'm so bored with boredom.
I've become boring.
But I'm bored of that too.... Argh.
Awesome...

From what i can remember:

Wednesday - A netball game with Team In Your Dreams. Steve flew in to a table sideways (he really can't see without his glasses y'know), Ash brought springs and inserted them in to his shoes because they wouldn't let him wear his wings on the court, Ben puked, I dislocated my knee and went home in an ambulance and Estar still doesn't know what's going on. Oh... and we got one goal. It was awesome! Can't wait for the next game. Of course, i won't be able to play anymore because i have my leg in a brace and i'm on crutches for 4 - 6 weeks but it's okay... i can't really play netball anyway.

My sweet left work and rushed himself to the hospital with a bag of my favourite munchies. He was all worried-like when he turned up. I think it was one of the most adorable things i've ever seen... Aww shit... my heart still melts when i think about it... Okay, okay, shut up now.

I must find out the name of the girl who put my knee back in place while i was screaming bloody murder. Apparently she was a vet...

Thursday - Recovering from Ashleys birthday party which happened after the netball game. I got back from the hospital at about midnight and decided that i wasn't going to deal with my new title as the token cripple just yet. By 7am the pain killers had worn off (so had everything else). I realised i was a cripple... and that Folkies was about to start.

Friday - I had spent a day coming down and a night at home feeling less than whatever i was before... Friday evening i'd made up my mind that i wasn't going to the Folkie. I didn't want to be the girl that everyone felt the need to "look after" just because i had a fucked knee.... and i was on crutches... and i couldn't really walk... or carry my own stuff... or drive.... yeah.... But then Mad told me that her sister Lucy (who is totally awesome) was in Canberra for the festival, so i got up and hobbled along (Lucy, if my leg never heals properly because i DIDN'T rest like i was supposed to... you'd better find a way to get me a new one).

Saturday, Sunday, Monday - Folkie, Folkie, Folkie! Ended up having a very decent time. Very glad i hobbled my way there every day. 'Twas well worth it. Pat became an Uncle on Monday to an adorable baby girl (insert gushy cutesy noises here). Everyone's doing well from what i hear. I can't wait to meet the little cherub.





Tuesday - Ah.... that was today wasn't it? Yeah, nothing happened today :-)

So...

Our little Mikey's all grown up.

It's his 21st party this Saturday!!!
(ask someone who can tell you the address ... and if you don't know someone who can tell you the address then you're probably not invited... and if you're not invited then it must really suck to be you.)

Your Leprechaun Name Is:
Wee McNugget
What's Your Leprechaun Name?

Cherry pop was very cool. Ashley & Jacqui brought the house down, just like i knew they would. Damn those chickies are an inspiration. Went back to Ashley, Ben and Steve's place after the gig to celebrate. Didn't get to bed before 6am. Didn't get to sleep before 7am but i was one of the lucky ones. Got about 5 hours sleep before being woken by an alarm - Got up - Ran around - bumped in to some shit - made a call - found out i wasn't needed after all.

Actually, what am i doing here? I should be trying to get some more sleeeeeeep now that i can.

What if i don't want any friends, Nickamc? You can't just walk past and see me using my laptop on lj and decide that we should be "friends."  :-)

(it's okay nuckmuck, i'll be your friend - by the way, i'm coming over after i've cut Ashley's hair - wait, i'll use my magic mobile phone for that msg!)

5 days without a Red Bull...

I just ate some red jelly for breakfast at lunchtime.... 9 hours of sleep at least.... yet i feel like i haven't slept.

Odd.

Going down to the Front Gallery tonight to watch some cherries get popped. Should be fun. It will be the "first time" for a whole bunch of newbie performers to get up on stage and do a half hour set.  As a member of Team Ashley & Jacqui, I'll be there to intimidate the competition by being that audience member with a stern and bored look on her face... and of course, to scream loudly when the girls perform.

That's totally not true by the way. I support all the newbies getting their cherries popped. In fact, i should probably do it next time. Or... the time after that... or, y'know, maybe the time after that.

Clearly, i'm way too chicken shit.

I didn't go uni..... Bad.

But i didn't drink any Red Bull either...... Good.

See? Everything evens out.

Except that Mad just dropped a Red Bull can and a mini bottle of Smirnoff in my lap.....Bad.

Hmmm....

But i'll be able to resist with the help of some spliff action.... GREAT.

Yep... everything really does even out.

Got Uni work piling up on my shoulders... I can feel it.
I don't actually know what it is because i'm too afraid to look in my diary. I probably shouldn't write this in my livejournal because people who know me will read it and then i'll just have more people on my back, trying to be casual in their reminders...

[Insert a calm, caring and somewhat authoritative voice here:]
"Kat, maybe you should.... y'know..... get some work done instead of.... hmmmm.... well, it's up to you."

Yeah, that's right. It IS up to me. It's a gorgeous day and i want to go outside and ... i dunno...... NOT do Uni.

W.H.I.N.G.E!


Fucking hell... i feel trapped.

I've gone 4 days without a red bull (trust me, this wasn't easy) and now i could really use one.... Fuck!

I could really do with a distraction.
